miRNA_target_sites_ESC

read the ESC RNA-seq data from TableS1 Denzler., et al., 2016

ESC_expression_data <- read.csv("TableS1_2016_sub.csv",header = TRUE)

count miR-294 target-sites

miR294 = 57000
miR294_6m = 0
miR294_7m = 0
miR294_8m = 0
for (i in 1:9545){
  miR294_6m = miR294_6m+ESC_expression_data[i,2]*ESC_expression_data[i,3]
  miR294_7m = miR294_7m+ESC_expression_data[i,2]*(ESC_expression_data[i,4]+ESC_expression_data[i,5])
  miR294_8m = miR294_8m+ESC_expression_data[i,2]*ESC_expression_data[i,6]
}
Graph<-barplot(c(miR294,miR294_6m,miR294_7m,miR294_8m),names.arg = c("miR294","6mer sites","7mer sites","8mer sites"),main = "miR294 and its target sites per ESC",ylim = c(0,70000))
text(x = Graph, y = c(miR294,miR294_6m,miR294_7m,miR294_8m), label = c(miR294,miR294_6m,miR294_7m,miR294_8m), pos = 3, cex = 0.8, col = "red")
